{
  "page": "House Harlton",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <p>This article is about content invented for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(2012_video_game)\" title=\"Game of Thrones (2012 video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> RPG video game developed by Cyanide Studio. Although this is a licensed derivative work based upon <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, it is not written by him.</p>\n<p>The material on this page should <i>not</i> be considered canonical for the novels, and is provided for informational purposes only.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Harlton of Castlewood</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Harlton.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Harlton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/62/House_Harlton.svg/250px-House_Harlton.svg.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/62/House_Harlton.svg/375px-House_Harlton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/62/House_Harlton.svg/500px-House_Harlton.svg.png 2x\" /></a></div></div><div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Coat of arms</th><td>\nA silver tree on green<br /><i>(Vert, a tree argent)</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Seat</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Castlewood\" title=\"Castlewood\">Castlewood</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">Riverlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Overlords</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tully\" title=\"House Tully\">House Tully</a> (AGOT)</li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Baelish\" title=\"House Baelish\">House Baelish</a> (ADWD)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Harlton of Castlewood</b> is a noble house from <a href=\"/index.php/Castlewood\" title=\"Castlewood\">Castlewood</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-VG_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-VG-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The family also owns a manse in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. They have thus far only been mentioned in the video game <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#House_Harlton_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">House Harlton at the end of the third century</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>Game of Thrones</i></span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Household\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Household</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Harlton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Because the Harltons were loyal to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> during <a href=\"/index.php/Robert%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Robert&#39;s Rebellion\">Robert's Rebellion</a>, Lord Harlton was executed for treason by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>. The late Lord Harlton's daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Marianne_Harlton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marianne Harlton\">Marianne</a>, was then raised by his heir and younger brother, the childless <a href=\"/index.php/Arwood_Harlton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arwood Harlton\">Arwood Harlton</a>. Lord Arwood became a friend of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Raynald_Sarwyck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Raynald Sarwyck\">Raynald Sarwyck</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-VG_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-VG-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Harlton_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">House Harlton at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Harlton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Harlton at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Harltons during the timespan of the events described in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>no member has appeared yet.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Game_of_Thrones\"><i>Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Harlton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Harltons appearing in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Arwood_Harlton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arwood Harlton\">Arwood Harlton</a>, Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Castlewood\" title=\"Castlewood\">Castlewood</a>.\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Marianne_Harlton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Marianne Harlton\">Marianne Harlton</a>, his niece.</li></ul></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Household\">Household</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Harlton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Household\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Martin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Martin\">Martin</a>, counselor, healer and tutor.</li>\n<li>Ser Desmond Hardyng, a knight.</li>\n<li>Ser Ethan of the Reach, captain of the guards.</li>\n<li>Alexander, a guard.</li>\n<li>Endrew, a guard.</li>\n<li>Domeric, a blacksmith.</li>\n<li>Shorei, a servant.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Harlton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-VG-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-VG_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-VG_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404080028\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.068 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.251 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 339/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 1910/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5125/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 763/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 6/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 474/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.170/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.44 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  239.036      1 -total\n 98.01%  234.284      1 Template:Noble_House\n 97.64%  233.391      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.37%   27.167     10 Template:Infobox_value\n  3.71%    8.879      3 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.71%    1.707      1 Template:Game\n  0.65%    1.543      1 Template:References\n  0.44%    1.048      1 Template:Mbox\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:21199-0!canonical and timestamp 202604